 12  lemma exists_forall_abs_polynomial_eval_le (p : polynomial ℂ) :
 13    ∃ x, ∀ y, (p.eval x).abs ≤ (p.eval y).abs :=
 14  if hp0 : 0 < degree p
 15  then let ⟨r, hr0, hr⟩ := polynomial.tendsto_infinity complex.abs hp0 ((p.eval 0).abs) in
 16    let ⟨x, hx₁, hx₂⟩ := (proper_space.compact_ball (0:ℂ) r).exists_forall_le
 17      ⟨0, by simp [le_of_lt hr0]⟩
 18      (continuous_abs.comp p.continuous_eval).continuous_on in
 19    ⟨x, λ y, if hy : y.abs ≤ r then hx₂ y $ by simpa [complex.dist_eq] using hy
 20      else le_trans (hx₂ _ (by simp [le_of_lt hr0])) (le_of_lt (hr y (lt_of_not_ge hy)))⟩
 21  else ⟨p.coeff 0, by rw [eq_C_of_degree_le_zero (le_of_not_gt hp0)]; simp⟩

 25  /-- The fundamental theorem of algebra. Every non constant complex polynomial
 26    has a root -/
